## (4)(a) Home Address vs Care-of Address

> What is the difference between Home Address (HA) and Care of Address (CoA)? *(5 marks)*

---

| Address | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Home Address (HoA)** | Permanent address assigned to mobile node, never changes |
| **Care-of Address (CoA)** | Temporary address acquired in visited network |

---

**Home Address:**
- Assigned by home network
- Used by correspondent nodes to reach the mobile
- Remains constant regardless of location
- Identifies the mobile node globally

**Care-of Address:**
- Acquired when mobile enters foreign network
- Changes each time mobile moves to new network
- Used for actual packet delivery
- Registered with Home Agent

> **Key insight:** Correspondents always send to Home Address. The Home Agent redirects to the current Care-of Address.

