## (4)(d) HMIPv6 vs Fast MIPv6 vs Proxy MIPv6

> Discuss the similarities and differences of Hierarchical Mobile IPv6 (HMIPv6) as compared to Fast and Proxy MIPv6. *(5 marks)*

---

**HMIPv6 (Hierarchical):**

::hmipv6

- Introduces **MAP (Mobility Anchor Point)** for local mobility
- Local moves only update MAP, not Home Agent
- Reduces signaling to home network

---

**Fast MIPv6:**

::fmipv6

- Reduces **handover latency** by anticipating moves
- Pre-configures new CoA before handover completes
- Near-zero packet loss during handover

---

**Proxy MIPv6:**

::pmipv6

- **Network-based** mobility (mobile doesn't participate)
- MAG (Mobile Access Gateway) handles mobility signaling
- Simpler for mobile devices, no MIP stack needed

---

**Comparison:**

| Aspect | HMIPv6 | FMIPv6 | PMIPv6 |
|--------|--------|--------|--------|
| **Goal** | Reduce signaling | Reduce latency | Simplify mobile |
| **New Entity** | MAP | None | MAG, LMA |
| **Mobile Involvement** | Yes | Yes | No |
| **Best For** | Frequent local moves | Real-time apps | Simple devices |

**Similarities:**
- All extend/improve base Mobile IP
- All maintain session continuity
- All aim to improve handover performance
